# Dev UI Testing Prerequisites

Before running dev UI validation (manual or Playwright), confirm all of the following:

- Use the current dev frontend URL from the latest deploy workflow, not a cached/old URL.
- Use an approved account with workbench/review permissions (for OTP flows, read the OTP from console in dev).
- Verify backend and frontend are from the same deploy cycle before investigating UI/API mismatches.
- Confirm the selected space/group context is valid for the account being tested.
- For review testing, open at least one session with reviewable assistant messages before assessing rating flow.
- Always check browser console and network for non-2xx API calls; include endpoint + status in findings.
